<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
<title>Brodeur Law Firm — Your Zoho System</title>
<style>
  /* IBM Plex embedded (self-contained, no external font fetch) */
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Sans';font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-display:swap;src:url(data:font/woff2;base64,) format('woff2');}
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Sans';font-style:normal;font-weight:500;font-display:swap;src:url(data:font/woff2;base64,) format('woff2');}
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Sans';font-style:normal;font-weight:600;font-display:swap;src:url(data:font/woff2;base64,) format('woff2');}
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Sans';font-style:normal;font-weight:700;font-display:swap;src:url(data:font/woff2;base64,) format('woff2');}
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Sans';font-style:italic;font-weight:400;font-display:swap;src:url(data:font/woff2;base64,) format('woff2');}
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono';font-style:normal;font-weight:400;font-display:swap;src:url(data:font/woff2;base64,) format('woff2');}
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono';font-style:normal;font-weight:500;font-display:swap;src:url(data:font/woff2;base64,) format('woff2');}
  @font-face{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono';font-style:normal;font-weight:600;font-display:swap;src:url(data:font/woff2;base64,) format('woff2');}

  /* =========================================================
     BRODEUR LAW × WOGGLE — system walkthrough (April)
     Look: Runbook (slate-teal, mono labels, squared status)
           + Memo-style action callout (tinted, left rule)
     Review actions live inline, on the component they concern.
     Print / .docx friendly.
     ========================================================= */
  :root{
    --ink:#1F2329; --body:#33383F; --muted:#5C636D; --faint:#878E98;
    --hair:#E7EAEE; --hair-strong:#D7DBE0; --rail:#F4F7F6;
    --live:#3C7A4B; --ready:#A9760F; --staged:#8A919B;
    --bg-around:#E8ECEC;
    --accent:#2C6E6A; --accent-deep:#224F4C; --sheet:#FDFDFC;
    --sans:"IBM Plex Sans",system-ui,sans-serif;
    --mono:"IBM Plex Mono",ui-monospace,monospace;
  }
  *{ box-sizing:border-box; }
  html{ -webkit-print-color-adjust:exact; print-color-adjust:exact; }
  body{ margin:0; background:var(--bg-around); color:var(--body); font-family:var(--sans); font-size:15px; line-height:1.65; -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased; text-rendering:optimizeLegibility; }
  a{ color:var(--accent-deep); }

  .page{ max-width:816px; margin:30px auto 70px; background:var(--sheet); padding:62px 76px 70px; border:1px solid var(--hair-strong); box-shadow:0 12px 36px rgba(20,30,50,.10); }

  /* ---------- header ---------- */
  .kicker{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:11.5px; letter-spacing:.14em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent-deep); margin-bottom:13px; }
  h1{ font-size:34px; line-height:1.12; letter-spacing:-.015em; color:var(--ink); font-weight:600; margin:0 0 13px; }
  .lede{ font-size:17px; line-height:1.58; color:var(--body); margin:0 0 26px; max-width:64ch; }

  dl.metabox{ border:1px solid var(--hair); border-radius:6px; overflow:hidden; margin:0 0 12px; }
  dl.metabox .row{ display:grid; grid-template-columns:150px 1fr; border-bottom:1px solid var(--hair); }
  dl.metabox .row:last-child{ border-bottom:none; }
  dl.metabox dt{ background:var(--rail); padding:9px 15px; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:11px; letter-spacing:.06em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--muted); border-right:1px solid var(--hair); }
  dl.metabox dd{ margin:0; padding:9px 15px; font-size:14px; color:var(--ink); }
  dl.metabox dd .mini{ color:var(--muted); }

  /* ---------- contents ---------- */
  .contents{ margin:30px 0 0; }
  .contents .c-h{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:11px; letter-spacing:.14em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--faint); margin-bottom:12px; padding-bottom:10px; border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--hair-strong); }
  .contents ol{ list-style:none; counter-reset:c; margin:0; padding:0; }
  .contents li{ counter-increment:c; }
  .contents a{ display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:12px; text-decoration:none; color:var(--ink); padding:7px 0; border-bottom:1px dotted var(--hair); }
  .contents a:hover{ color:var(--accent-deep); }
  .contents a::before{ content:counter(c,decimal-leading-zero); font-family:var(--mono); font-size:12px; color:var(--accent-deep); flex:none; width:24px; }
  .contents .ct{ flex:1; }

  /* ---------- generic section ---------- */
  .sec{ margin-top:44px; padding-top:28px; border-top:1px solid var(--hair); }
  .sec-eyebrow{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:12px; letter-spacing:.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent-deep); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:7px; }
  .sec h2{ font-size:23px; line-height:1.2; letter-spacing:-.01em; color:var(--ink); font-weight:600; margin:0 0 14px; }
  p{ margin:0 0 14px; max-width:68ch; }
  .muted{ color:var(--muted); }

  /* ---------- status token (squared, uppercase) ---------- */
  .st{ display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:7px; white-space:nowrap; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:11px; font-weight:500; letter-spacing:.07em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--muted); }
  .st .dot{ width:9px; height:9px; border-radius:2px; flex:none; }
  .st.live{ color:var(--live); } .st.live .dot{ background:var(--live); }
  .st.ready{ color:var(--ready); } .st.ready .dot{ background:var(--ready); }
  .st.staged{ color:var(--staged); } .st.staged .dot{ background:var(--staged); }

  /* ---------- key / legend table ---------- */
  table.key{ width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; border:1px solid var(--hair); border-radius:6px; overflow:hidden; }
  table.key td{ padding:12px 16px; border-bottom:1px solid var(--hair); vertical-align:top; }
  table.key tr:last-child td{ border-bottom:none; }
  table.key td.k{ width:165px; background:var(--rail); border-right:1px solid var(--hair); }
  table.key td.v{ color:var(--muted); font-size:14px; }

  /* ---------- journey table ---------- */
  table.flow{ width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; }
  table.flow th{ text-align:left; font-family:var(--mono); font-weight:500; font-size:10.5px; letter-spacing:.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--faint); padding:0 14px 9px 0; border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--hair-strong); }
  table.flow th.s-h{ text-align:right; padding-right:0; }
  table.flow td{ padding:11px 14px 11px 0; border-bottom:1px solid var(--hair); vertical-align:middle; }
  table.flow td.n{ width:30px; font-family:var(--mono); color:var(--faint); font-size:13px; }
  table.flow td.ph{ font-weight:600; color:var(--ink); }
  table.flow td.fo{ color:var(--muted); font-size:14px; }
  table.flow td.s{ text-align:right; padding-right:0; }
  table.flow a{ color:inherit; text-decoration:none; }
  table.flow tr:last-child td{ border-bottom:none; }

  /* ---------- components table ---------- */
  table.comp{ width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:6px 0 4px; }
  table.comp caption{ text-align:left; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:10.5px; letter-spacing:.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--faint); padding:0 0 9px; }
  table.comp th{ text-align:left; font-family:var(--mono); font-weight:500; font-size:10.5px; letter-spacing:.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--faint); padding:0 14px 8px 0; border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--hair-strong); }
  table.comp th.s-h{ text-align:right; padding-right:0; }
  table.comp td{ padding:12px 14px 12px 0; border-bottom:1px solid var(--hair); vertical-align:top; }
  table.comp td.c{ width:34%; font-weight:600; color:var(--ink); }
  table.comp td.d{ color:var(--muted); font-size:14px; }
  table.comp td.s{ text-align:right; padding-right:0; white-space:nowrap; }
  table.comp tr:last-child td{ border-bottom:none; }

  /* ---------- inline REVIEW prompt (lives in the component's row) ---------- */
  .rev{ display:grid; grid-template-columns:17px 1fr; gap:10px; margin:10px 0 2px;
        background:color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 6%, var(--sheet));
        border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 22%, var(--hair));
        border-left:3px solid var(--accent); border-radius:5px; padding:10px 13px; }
  .rev .chk{ width:15px; height:15px; margin-top:2px; border:1.5px solid var(--accent); border-radius:3px; background:#fff; flex:none; }
  .rev .rtag{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:10px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent-deep); }
  .rev .rtxt{ display:block; font-size:13.5px; line-height:1.5; color:var(--ink); margin-top:3px; }
  .rev a{ color:var(--accent-deep); text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:2px; text-decoration-thickness:1px; font-weight:500; white-space:nowrap; }
  .rev .links{ margin-top:5px; display:block; }

  /* ✎ Provide note (component row) — amber sibling of .rev */
  .prov{ display:grid; grid-template-columns:17px 1fr; gap:10px; margin:10px 0 2px;
        background:color-mix(in srgb, var(--ready) 7%, var(--sheet));
        border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--ready) 26%, var(--hair));
        border-left:3px solid var(--ready); border-radius:5px; padding:10px 13px; }
  .prov .chk{ width:15px; height:15px; margin-top:2px; border:1.5px solid var(--ready); border-radius:3px; background:#fff; flex:none; }
  .prov .ptag{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:10px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--ready); }
  .prov .rtxt{ display:block; font-size:13.5px; line-height:1.5; color:var(--ink); margin-top:3px; }
  .prov a{ color:var(--accent-deep); text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:2px; text-decoration-thickness:1px; font-weight:500; }
  .prov .links{ margin-top:5px; display:block; }
  table.lib td.yp{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:10.5px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:.05em; text-transform:uppercase; white-space:nowrap; }
  .yp.review{ color:var(--accent-deep); } .yp.provide{ color:var(--ready); } .yp.later, .yp.none{ color:var(--faint); }

  /* ---------- phase status line ---------- */
  .phase-status{ display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin:-4px 0 16px; padding:9px 14px; background:var(--rail); border:1px solid var(--hair); border-radius:5px; }
  .phase-status .txt{ font-size:13.5px; color:var(--muted); }

  /* ---------- ACTION REQUIRED callout (Memo style: tinted, left rule) ---------- */
  .action{ margin:22px 0 6px; border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 22%, var(--hair)); border-left:3px solid var(--accent); border-radius:5px; background:color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 5%, var(--sheet)); padding:16px 20px 18px; break-inside:avoid; }
  .action .a-lbl{ display:flex; align-items:center; gap:9px; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:11px; letter-spacing:.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent-deep); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px; }
  .action .a-lbl .cnt{ color:var(--faint); font-weight:500; letter-spacing:.06em; white-space:nowrap; }
  .action ul{ list-style:none; margin:8px 0 0; padding:0; }
  .action li{ display:grid; grid-template-columns:18px 1fr; gap:11px; padding:11px 0; border-bottom:1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 16%, var(--hair)); }
  .action li:last-child{ border-bottom:none; }
  .chk{ width:16px; height:16px; margin-top:3px; border:1.5px solid var(--accent); border-radius:3px; background:#fff; flex:none; }
  .a-text{ font-size:14.5px; line-height:1.55; color:var(--ink); }
  .a-lead{ font-weight:700; letter-spacing:.01em; margin-right:3px; }
  .a-lead.provide{ color:#4B5563; }
  .a-lead.decide{ color:var(--ready); }
  .a-text a{ color:var(--accent-deep); text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:2px; text-decoration-thickness:1px; }
  .rec{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:var(--live); background:#E2EFDA; border-radius:3px; padding:1px 7px; margin-left:3px; white-space:nowrap; }
  .a-note{ font-size:13px; color:var(--muted); margin-top:12px; padding-top:11px; border-top:1px dashed color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 18%, var(--hair)); }
  .a-note b{ color:var(--ink); }

  /* lightweight "nothing to do" note (for fully-live phases) */
  .done-note{ margin:20px 0 6px; padding:12px 16px; border:1px solid #CDE3D3; background:#F1F8F2; border-radius:5px; font-size:13.5px; color:var(--body); }
  .done-note .ok{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:11px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:.06em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--live); margin-right:7px; }
  .done-note b{ color:var(--ink); }

  /* ---------- library ---------- */
  .lib-sum{ display:flex; gap:18px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin:0 0 16px; padding:11px 16px; background:var(--rail); border:1px solid var(--hair); border-radius:5px; }
  table.lib{ width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; }
  table.lib th{ text-align:left; font-family:var(--mono); font-weight:500; font-size:10.5px; letter-spacing:.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--faint); padding:0 14px 8px 0; border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--hair-strong); }
  table.lib th.s-h{ text-align:right; padding-right:0; }
  table.lib td{ padding:10px 14px 10px 0; border-bottom:1px solid var(--hair); vertical-align:middle; }
  table.lib td.nm{ font-weight:600; color:var(--ink); width:42%; }
  table.lib td.ty{ color:var(--muted); font-family:var(--mono); font-size:12.5px; }
  table.lib td.s{ text-align:right; padding-right:0; white-space:nowrap; }
  table.lib tr:last-child td{ border-bottom:none; }
  table.lib td.nm a{ color:var(--accent-deep); text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:2px; text-decoration-thickness:1px; }

  /* ---------- closer ---------- */
  ol.need{ list-style:none; counter-reset:n; margin:14px 0 18px; padding:0; display:grid; gap:14px; }
  ol.need li{ display:grid; grid-template-columns:26px 1fr; gap:13px; }
  ol.need li::before{ counter-increment:n; content:counter(n); width:24px; height:24px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--ink); color:#fff; font-family:var(--mono); font-weight:600; font-size:12px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; }
  ol.need .nh{ font-weight:600; color:var(--ink); }
  ol.need .nb{ color:var(--muted); font-size:14px; }
  .kicker-note{ background:color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 5%, var(--sheet)); border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 20%, var(--hair)); border-radius:5px; padding:13px 16px; font-size:14.5px; color:var(--body); }
  .kicker-note b{ color:var(--ink); }
  footer.docfoot{ margin-top:38px; padding-top:18px; border-top:1px solid var(--hair); font-family:var(--mono); font-size:11px; color:var(--faint); letter-spacing:.03em; }

  /* ---------- print ---------- */
  @page{ size:Letter; margin:16mm 18mm; }
  @media print{
    body{ background:#fff; }
    .page{ box-shadow:none; border:none; margin:0; max-width:none; padding:0; }
    .contents{ break-after:page; }
    .sec, .action, .rev, table.comp tr, table.lib tr, table.flow tr{ break-inside:avoid; }
    .sec h2, table.comp caption, .phase-status{ break-after:avoid; }
  }
  @media (max-width:680px){
    .page{ padding:34px 22px 44px; margin:0; }
    h1{ font-size:28px; }
    dl.metabox .row, table.key tr{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }
    table.comp td.c{ width:auto; }
  }
  /* component-name link -> primary workflow rule */
  table.comp td.c a.clink{ color:var(--ink); text-decoration:none; border-bottom:1px solid var(--hair-strong); transition:color .12s, border-color .12s; }
  table.comp td.c a.clink:hover{ color:var(--accent-deep); border-color:var(--accent); }
  .ar{ color:var(--accent); font-size:.82em; vertical-align:1px; }
  /* workflows reference */
  table.lib td.nm .sub{ display:block; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:10px; font-weight:400; letter-spacing:0; text-transform:none; color:var(--faint); margin-top:3px; }
  table.lib tr.grp td{ font-family:var(--mono); font-size:10px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent-deep); padding:18px 0 7px; border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--hair-strong); }
  table.lib tr.grp:first-child td{ padding-top:2px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="page">

  <!-- ===== HEADER ===== -->
  <header>
    <div class="kicker">System Reference · Brodeur Law Firm × Woggle Consulting</div>
    <h1>Your Zoho system, end to end</h1>
    <p class="lede">A plain-English reference for the system that now runs your client journey — what each part does, whether it's running yet, and the few things I need from you to switch on what's ready.</p>
    <dl class="metabox">
      <div class="row"><dt>Audience</dt><dd>April Brodeur · Managing Attorney</dd></div>
      <div class="row"><dt>Maintained by</dt><dd>Jed Thomas · Woggle Consulting</dd></div>
      <div class="row"><dt>Last updated</dt><dd>June 2026 <span class="mini">· v1.4</span></dd></div>
      <div class="row"><dt>System status</dt><dd><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>11 Live</span> &nbsp; <span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>22 Ready</span> &nbsp; <span class="st staged"><span class="dot"></span>2 Staged</span></dd></div>
    </dl>
  </header>

  <!-- ===== CONTENTS ===== -->
  <nav class="contents" aria-label="Contents">
    <div class="c-h">Contents</div>
    <ol>
      <li><a href="#overview"><span class="ct">Overview</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#how-to-use"><span class="ct">How to use this document</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#status-key"><span class="ct">Status key</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#journey"><span class="ct">The client journey</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#phase-1"><span class="ct">Phase 1 — New Inquiry &amp; Lead Intake</span><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#phase-2"><span class="ct">Phase 2 — Intro Call &amp; Planning Session Prep</span><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#phase-3"><span class="ct">Phase 3 — Post-Planning: Billing &amp; Design Worksheet</span><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#phase-4"><span class="ct">Phase 4 — The Design Meeting</span><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#phase-5"><span class="ct">Phase 5 — Post-Design Meeting &amp; Estate Plan Summary</span><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#phase-6"><span class="ct">Phase 6 — Drafting, Signing, Binder &amp; Three-Year Review</span><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Mixed</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#library"><span class="ct">Email &amp; text library</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#tasks"><span class="ct">Internal tasks &amp; reminders</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#workflows"><span class="ct">Workflow automations</span></a></li>
      <li><a href="#what-we-need"><span class="ct">What I need from you</span></a></li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- ===== OVERVIEW ===== -->
  <section id="overview" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Section 1</div>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>This is the single reference for the automated system behind your client journey in Zoho. The journey runs in <strong>six phases</strong>, from a first inquiry through drafting, signing, and the three-year review. One automated path carries each matter along — with you at every decision point, and your own SOPs as the blueprint underneath.</p>
    <p>Each phase below is documented the same way: a short description of what happens, a table of the components in the system and their status, and — where something needs your input — a <strong>Review</strong> prompt right on the item, plus an <strong>Action required</strong> box for anything to provide or decide. Behind these client-facing emails, the same automations also create the staff and attorney tasks that move each matter along — those are catalogued in <a href="#tasks">Internal tasks &amp; reminders</a>. Nothing here is urgent; work through it at your own pace.</p>
    <p class="muted" style="font-size:13.5px;">One distinction worth keeping in mind as you read: <em>“the automation is built”</em> and <em>“the wording is final”</em> are two different things. An automation can be finished and tested while the copy inside its emails still needs your sign-off — so a built item can still be waiting on a word or two from you. Where that's the case, it's flagged.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== HOW TO USE ===== -->
  <section id="how-to-use" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Section 2</div>
    <h2>How to use this document</h2>
    <p>Read top to bottom, or jump to a phase from the contents above. Anything that needs your input is one of three kinds:</p>
    <table class="key">
      <tr><td class="k"><span class="rtag" style="color:var(--accent-deep);font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:600;">▸ Review</span></td><td class="v">Sits right under the component it concerns. Open the finished item, read it the way a client would, and confirm it's right. Each one links straight into the template in Zoho.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="k"><span class="a-lead provide">✎ Provide</span></td><td class="v">Flagged right on any message that's still empty (and in the <strong>Action required</strong> box). The message links to its template in Zoho; you add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="k"><span class="a-lead decide">Decide</span></td><td class="v">Also in <strong>Action required</strong> — make a small choice. Each has a recommended default you can simply approve.</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="muted" style="margin-top:13px;font-size:13.5px;">Underlined text is a link. Checkboxes are there so you can tick items off as you go.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== STATUS KEY ===== -->
  <section id="status-key" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Section 3</div>
    <h2>Status key</h2>
    <p>Every component and message carries one of three states:</p>
    <table class="key">
      <tr><td class="k"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td><td class="v">It's running in your system right now.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="k"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td><td class="v">Finished and tested — we just need your final content and sign-off before we turn it on.</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="k"><span class="st staged"><span class="dot"></span>Staged</span></td><td class="v">Designed and on the roadmap, but not built yet.</td></tr>
    </table>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== JOURNEY ===== -->
  <section id="journey" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Section 4</div>
    <h2>The client journey</h2>
    <p>The six phases, in order, and where each one stands today:</p>
    <table class="flow">
      <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Phase</th><th>Focus</th><th class="s-h">Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="n">1</td><td class="ph"><a href="#phase-1">New Inquiry &amp; Lead Intake</a></td><td class="fo">Capture &amp; first contact</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="n">2</td><td class="ph"><a href="#phase-2">Intro Call &amp; Planning-Session Prep</a></td><td class="fo">Book &amp; prepare the session</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="n">3</td><td class="ph"><a href="#phase-3">Billing &amp; Design Worksheet</a></td><td class="fo">Payment &amp; the two-gate rule</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="n">4</td><td class="ph"><a href="#phase-4">The Design Meeting</a></td><td class="fo">Remind, meet &amp; review</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="n">5</td><td class="ph"><a href="#phase-5">Estate Plan Summary</a></td><td class="fo">Approve the plan, set up drafting</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="n">6</td><td class="ph"><a href="#phase-6">Signing, Binder &amp; 3-Year Review</a></td><td class="fo">Execute &amp; stay in touch</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Mixed</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PHASE 1 ===== -->
  <section id="phase-1" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Phase 1</div>
    <h2>New Inquiry &amp; Lead Intake</h2>
    <div class="phase-status"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span><span class="txt">Live and running — one closing email still needs your wording.</span></div>
    <p>A new potential client can come in two ways: through your website inquiry form, or entered by staff at the kiosk. Either way, a lead is created automatically and the right first email goes out based on where they came from. Leads that don't book get a courteous closing email instead.</p>
    <table class="comp">
      <caption>Components</caption>
      <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>What it does</th><th class="s-h">Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000003681075" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Inquiry intake (form + kiosk) <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Creates the lead automatically from either source.</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000003504030" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lead-source welcome emails <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Sends the right intro email based on lead source.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">Read it as a brand-new client would: check the greeting sounds like you, the firm details are right, and the next step is obvious.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000000792025" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Inquiry Thank-You ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000003504030" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lead magnets <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">“Wills vs. Trusts” and “Kids Protection Plan” guides go out on request.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">Skim both guides for accuracy and voice — confirm the explanations match how you'd describe them to a client.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000003138029" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wills vs. Trusts ↗</a> &nbsp; <a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000003138022" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kids Protection Plan ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000000917637" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Did-Not-Book closing <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Leads that don't book an intro call get a closing email — its wording is still a placeholder.
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">Still empty — add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000000917127" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open lead closing email ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="action">
      <div class="a-lbl">▸ Action required <span class="cnt">— 1 item</span></div>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead provide">Provide.</span>The closing email for leads who don’t book (it’s currently a “Type your text here…” placeholder) — <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open your content doc</a>.</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="a-note"><b>Otherwise, Phase 1 runs on its own.</b> Want to see it work? Submit a test inquiry on your own site (use your email) and watch the reply land.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PHASE 2 ===== -->
  <section id="phase-2" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Phase 2</div>
    <h2>Intro Call &amp; Planning Session Prep</h2>
    <div class="phase-status"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span><span class="txt">Running — a few reminder emails still need your wording.</span></div>
    <p>This is the stretch from the 15-minute intro call through the Planning Session. When a session is booked, the system creates the matter in your Intake pipeline, sends the intake homework on an automatic reminder schedule, and assigns staff their prep tasks. When the engagement agreement is signed, the client's WorkDrive folders are created and the matter moves into the Estate Planning pipeline.</p>
    <table class="comp">
      <caption>Components</caption>
      <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>What it does</th><th class="s-h">Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000000635148" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Planning Session booking <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Books via Bookings; auto-creates the matter in the Intake pipeline, and sends your New Client Welcome.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">Open it and fill in the resource links it’s built to share — the Homework Instructions PDF, the “What Is a Trust?” and Legacy Planning Overview videos, and the Wills vs. Trusts brochure (each is still a “[Insert … Here]” placeholder) — then read it through to confirm it sounds like you.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000000792319" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open New Client Welcome ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000000712362" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Intake homework + reminders <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Sends the homework and reminds at 4 wks, 3 wks, 2 wks, 10 days, and 1 wk. <em>(Schedule is live; the reminder wording is still being finalized — see below.)</em>
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">Still empty — add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000006891034" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open the homework emails ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000000714199" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Homework tracking &amp; staff review <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Tracks status (Sent → Submitted → Reviewed) and assigns review tasks.</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000008102168" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Folder prep checklist <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Creates the staff task to prepare the Planning Session folder.</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000001440037" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Engagement signing (Zoho Sign) <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">On signing: creates WorkDrive folders and switches the matter to Estate Planning.</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000000926486" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LawPay client setup <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Creates the client in LawPay so billing is ready.</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="action">
      <div class="a-lbl">▸ Action required <span class="cnt">— 2 items</span></div>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead provide">Provide.</span>The intake homework reminder wording and the staff point-person introduction — <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open your content doc</a>.</span></li>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead decide">Decide.</span>How many homework reminders, and how far apart. <span class="rec">✓ Recommended</span> keep the current five-touch schedule (4 wks, 3 wks, 2 wks, 10 days, 1 wk) — approve as-is, or tell me to change it.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PHASE 3 ===== -->
  <section id="phase-3" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Phase 3</div>
    <h2>Post-Planning Session — Billing &amp; Design Worksheet</h2>
    <div class="phase-status"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span><span class="txt">Built and tested — ready to switch on once your content is confirmed.</span></div>
    <p>This covers everything after the client decides to move forward: billing, the Design Worksheet, and getting them to a Design Meeting. The centerpiece is the <strong>two-gate rule</strong> that holds a matter in place until both the money and the homework are in.</p>
    <table class="comp">
      <caption>Components</caption>
      <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>What it does</th><th class="s-h">Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000000726226" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Invoice payment reminders <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Every-other-day email + text until paid; “pay at least 5 business days before the Design Meeting.”
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">Still empty — add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007491303" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open invoice reminder ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c">Payment confirmation</td><td class="d">Auto-sends a $0-balance PDF when payment lands.</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000008471121" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Attorney's post-session routing <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Did Not Engage / Undecided / Design Meeting Scheduled / To Be Scheduled.</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007266335" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Undecided follow-up series <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Gentle weekly follow-ups for clients still deciding.
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">Still empty — add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214025" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open undecided follow-up ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275066" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Did Not Engage closing <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Closing email, with separate paid and unpaid versions.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">Read both versions, and confirm the paid one explains the refund clearly.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214032" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Did Not Engage — paid ↗</a> &nbsp; <a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214039" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Did Not Engage — unpaid ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275229" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Design Worksheet send + thank-you <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Sends the worksheet, and a thank-you when it's returned.
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">The worksheet’s cover note and thank-you wording are still needed — add them in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275205" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Two-gate auto-advance <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Holds until invoice paid AND worksheet returned, then advances on its own.</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="action">
      <div class="a-lbl">▸ Action required <span class="cnt">— 2 items</span></div>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead provide">Provide.</span>Invoice, Design Worksheet, and “undecided” reminder wording — <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open your content doc</a>.</span></li>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead decide">Decide.</span>The two-gate rule (paid AND worksheet back), the every-other-day payment rhythm, and the Design Worksheet's format. <span class="rec">✓ Recommended</span> keep all three as built — approve, or flag what to change.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PHASE 4 ===== -->
  <section id="phase-4" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Phase 4</div>
    <h2>The Design Meeting</h2>
    <div class="phase-status"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span><span class="txt">Built and tested — ready to switch on.</span></div>
    <p>Appointment reminders lead up to the meeting; during it, decisions are captured in the design form; and scheduling the Design Review Meeting (DRM) kicks off its own reminder series that stops the moment the client approves their Estate Plan Summary.</p>
    <table class="comp">
      <caption>Components</caption>
      <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>What it does</th><th class="s-h">Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275118" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Design Meeting prep email <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Goes to the client once their Design Meeting is booked — what to expect and how to prepare.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">This one reaches every client, so give it a close read: confirm the prep steps and tone are exactly how you'd want them set up for the meeting.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214053" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open DM Preparation email ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275153" target="_blank" rel="noopener">“Time to schedule” reminder <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Nudges clients who still need to book their Design Meeting.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">Confirm it reads the way you want, and that the booking link is easy to spot.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214046" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open “time to schedule” reminder ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275153" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Auto-cancel notice <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">If a meeting isn't confirmed in time, sends a courteous cancel-and-rebook note.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">Confirm it closes the loop kindly and makes rebooking effortless.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214060" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open auto-cancel notice ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007393649" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Appointment reminders (email + text) <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Reminders at 10 days, 1 week, and 3 business days out.
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">Still empty — add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007393668" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open appointment reminders ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007393225" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DRM confirmation &amp; reminders <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Confirms the Design Review Meeting and reminds the client.
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">Still empty — add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007393208" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open DRM confirmation ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275359" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DRM stop condition <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Reminders stop and the DRM cancels when the client approves their EPS.</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275256" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meeting recording task <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Reminds you to upload the Teams recording to the matter.</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="action">
      <div class="a-lbl">▸ Action required <span class="cnt">— 2 items</span></div>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead provide">Provide.</span>The appointment-reminder and Design Review confirmation wording — <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open your content doc</a>.</span></li>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead decide">Decide.</span>How close to the meeting it should auto-cancel an unconfirmed booking. <span class="rec">✓ Recommended</span> 2 business days — approve, or set your own window.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PHASE 5 ===== -->
  <section id="phase-5" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Phase 5</div>
    <h2>Post-Design Meeting &amp; Estate Plan Summary</h2>
    <div class="phase-status"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span><span class="txt">Built and tested — ready to switch on.</span></div>
    <p>After the Design Meeting, the system shepherds the Estate Plan Summary from preparation through client approval, then sets up drafting — so nothing is re-keyed when the matter moves to WealthDocx.</p>
    <table class="comp">
      <caption>Components</caption>
      <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>What it does</th><th class="s-h">Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275280" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Finalize Design path <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">If the design isn't finished in the meeting: attorney task + daily reminders.</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275280" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Prepare EPS <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Paralegal tasks to export, edit, and upload the EPS; then your review.</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275280" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EPS Ready for Review <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Notifies the client; reminders every 2 days until they approve.
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">Still empty — add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214067" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open EPS Ready for Review ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275359" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EPS Approved <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Congratulations email; matter marked ready to draft.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">A nice milestone moment — confirm it reads the way you want and the “what happens next” is clear.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214074" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open EPS Approved ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275391" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Drafter / WealthDocx setup <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Assigns the drafter and preps the contact CSV for WealthDocx.</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="action">
      <div class="a-lbl">▸ Action required <span class="cnt">— 2 items</span></div>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead provide">Provide.</span>The EPS messages — the “EPS Ready for Review” note and the every-2-day review reminders — <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open your content doc</a>.</span></li>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead decide">Decide.</span>How a client signs off on their Estate Plan Summary. <span class="rec">✓ Recommended</span> a single approve action in their portal, which trips the stop condition and ends the reminders automatically.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== PHASE 6 ===== -->
  <section id="phase-6" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Phase 6</div>
    <h2>Drafting, Signing, Binder &amp; Three-Year Review</h2>
    <div class="phase-status"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Mixed</span><span class="txt">Some live, several ready to review, and the post-binder &amp; three-year work staged for the next build.</span></div>
    <p>The pipeline stages for the whole lifecycle already exist — a matter can travel from drafting to binder delivery to the three-year follow-up. Several signing automations are built and switched off, your Will and Trust pre-signing emails are fully designed, and binder delivery already requests a Google review. The post-binder reminder cadences and the three-year review are designed but not yet built.</p>
    <table class="comp">
      <caption>Components</caption>
      <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>What it does</th><th class="s-h">Status</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275548" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pre-signing prep emails (Will / Trust) <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Your full Canva-designed preparation emails.
          <div class="rev"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="rtag">▸ Review</span><span class="rtxt">No rush — these are for a later phase — but whenever you have a moment, confirm both read the way you want.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007275522" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pre-Signing Prep — Will ↗</a> &nbsp; <a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214095" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pre-Signing Prep — Trust ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007393508" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Signing scheduling &amp; reminders <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Confirmation, tentative, and booking-reminder automations.
          <div class="prov"><span class="chk"></span><span><span class="ptag">✎ Provide</span><span class="rtxt">Still empty — add the wording in your <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content doc</a>.</span><span class="links"><a href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/templates?type=email&step=edit&templateId=6678359000007214081" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open signing emails ↗</a></span></span></div>
        </td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000007275595" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Signing-prep checklists (print, tab, assemble) <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Staff checklist tasks for signing-day prep.</td><td class="s"><span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000008102210" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Binder delivery &amp; closeout <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Staff tasks prep and close out the binder; the Google-review request is set to follow once its wording is written.</td><td class="s"><span class="st live"><span class="dot"></span>Live</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c"><a class="clink" href="https://crm.zoho.com/crm/org882398583/settings/workflow-rules/6678359000008441052" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Post-binder reminders <span class="ar">↗</span></a></td><td class="d">Trust-funding, annual check-in, and beneficiary reminders.</td><td class="s"><span class="st staged"><span class="dot"></span>Staged</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td class="c">Three-Year Review</td><td class="d">Automated worksheet + categorized response handling.</td><td class="s"><span class="st staged"><span class="dot"></span>Staged</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="action">
      <div class="a-lbl">▸ Action required <span class="cnt">— when ready</span></div>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead provide">Provide.</span>Your signing emails and the Google review request wording, whenever you're ready for this phase — <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">open your content doc</a>.</span></li>
        <li><span class="chk"></span><span class="a-text"><span class="a-lead decide">Decide.</span>When the three-year-review clock starts. <span class="rec">✓ Recommended</span> at signing (not binder delivery), so the date is fixed the moment the plan is executed.</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="a-note"><b>No rush.</b> The post-binder and three-year pieces are the next build — there's nothing to turn on here yet. These answers just let me build them the way you work.</p>
