  <!-- ===== WHAT WE NEED ===== -->
  <section id="what-we-need" class="sec">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Reference</div>
    <h2>What I need from you</h2>
    <p>To switch on everything marked <span class="st ready"><span class="dot"></span>Ready</span>, there are three kinds of things I need — and you can hand them over in any order.</p>
    <ol class="need">
      <li><span><span class="nh">Content.</span> <span class="nb">The wording for the “Ready” items — the intake and invoice reminders, Design Worksheet text, undecided and EPS-review nudges, and the Design Review confirmation. It all lives in one place: <a href="https://documents.woggleconsulting.com/external/writer/bba91ef559ac698d9cddfd5e285a151b022d3fff8acd5a56717290abfb329103" target="_blank" rel="noopener">your content doc</a>. Just type into the labeled spaces; I'll handle subject lines, links, and formatting.</span></span></li>
      <li><span><span class="nh">Decisions.</span> <span class="nb">A handful of small choices — the homework reminder cadence, the two-gate rule, the auto-cancel window, how clients approve the EPS, and when the three-year clock starts. Each has a recommended default; just approve it, or tell me what to change.</span></span></li>
      <li><span><span class="nh">A read-through.</span> <span class="nb">Work down the <strong>Review</strong> prompts in each phase, read those items as a client would, and flag anything that sounds off. That's the only review I need before we go live.</span></span></li>
    </ol>
    <div class="kicker-note">Do it at your own pace — there's no wrong order, and nothing breaks if you pause. <b>The fastest path: approve the recommended defaults and fill in the content doc.</b> We can refine any of it later, and walk through anything you like together on our call.</div>
    <footer class="docfoot">Brodeur Law Firm × Woggle Consulting · System walkthrough · v1.4 · Updated June 2026 · Confidential</footer>
  </section>

</div>

